<item>
            <title>[JCR-1347] Move Jackrabbit Query Parser from core to spi-commons</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1347</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The query parser can be used outside jackrabbit-core, for instances in other repository implementations based on JCR2SPI.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Proposal:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- move source and build infrastructure from o.a.j.core.query to o.a.j.spi.commons.query&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- switch over jackrabbit.core to use spi-commons for query&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
- optimally, add specific test cases for the query tree generation. </description>
